President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of New York due to severe storms and flooding caused by Tropical Depression Ida and a nor'easter that occurred from November 12-14, 2009. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts in Nassau and Suffolk counties. The funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures statewide. Albert Lewis has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.